Concerto: a set of tools to extract, analyse and browse certificates and chains:
 - piatto, a Parsifal-based tool to extract certificates from answer dumps

 - chitarra, an OCaml tool to enrich data in the database

 - piccolo, a web server in Python/Flask to present the result
 - fagotto, a program to produce report

 - maestro, to wrap it up


Currently, we need to call some programs one after the other:
 - piatto-lite (*.dump -> answers.csv + chains.csv + raw/ [certs])
 - merge-certs (fusion des raw/certs/*)
 - parseCerts (certs/* -> certs.csv + dns.csv + names.csv + unparsed.csv
 - prepareLinks [Needs to see the whole certs.csv!]



= Example on a campaign =

make -j 8 $( for i in 0[67]*/?/*.dump; do echo ${i/.dump/.piatto}; done )

~/dev/research/concerto/piatto-lite/mergeRawFiles -t certs -o common $(for x in 0[67]*/?/*.piatto; do echo -i $x; done) $(for i in $(seq 0 255); do printf "%2.2x " $i; done) -v

for i in 0[45]*/?/*.piatto/raw/certs/*.pack; do rm -f $i; done

sort -u 0[45]*/?/*.piatto/chains.csv > chains.csv

parseCerts -o parsed-certs -i common -t certs 00 01

prepareLinks ...

checkLinks

buildChains

gradeChains?